The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of neural machine translation using GPUs, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of deep learning models, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of mini-batching and k-best extraction algorithms, which are common optimization techniques in neural networks and could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of GPUs for efficient implementation, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as GPUs are commonly used for image processing tasks.
